This paper deals with mechanism design, which is a subfield of game theory (cs.GT). The paper specifically focuses on the interplay between incentive compatibility and envy freeness, which are both important concepts in mechanism design. Therefore, cs.AI (artificial intelligence) and cs.EC (economics and computation) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also uses mathematical tools such as cyclic monotonicity and local efficiency, which are commonly used in optimization and algorithm design, making cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses Pareto-optimal mechanisms, which are often studied in the context of machine learning and decision making, making cs.LG (machine learning) a possible sub-category as well.
